WEBVTT

00:02.043 --> 00:03.044
PREVIOUSLY ON "REVENGE"...
 I AM AMANDA CLARKE.

00:03.044 --> 00:04.885
"WHAT KIND OF DETECTIVE
DOESN'T KNOW THE REAL NAME

00:04.885 --> 00:06.547
OF THE WOMAN
THAT HE'S BEEN DATING?"

00:06.547 --> 00:09.430
THE THING WITH LOUISE --
IT'S NOT A TRADITIONAL MARRIAGE.

00:09.430 --> 00:13.094
THEN WHY LIE TO HER?
 EMILY AND NOLAN
ARE STRANGERS TO HONESTY.

00:13.094 --> 00:14.685
THERE'S SO MUCH MORE
YOU DON'T KNOW.

00:14.685 --> 00:15.806
I WANT THE TRUTH.

00:15.806 --> 00:18.139
I RAN A DIAGNOSTIC.
FILES WERE COPIED.

00:18.139 --> 00:20.561
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHAT YOU'VE EXPOSED ME TO?!

00:20.561 --> 00:22.563
THE WHOLE WORLD IS
DYING TO HEAR YOUR STORY.

00:22.563 --> 00:25.106
VICTORIA SCHEMED,
PLOTTED, AND RAILED

00:25.106 --> 00:27.408
AGAINST ME,
MY FRIENDS, AND LOVED ONES.

00:27.408 --> 00:30.030
AMANDA CLARKE HAS
DUG A GRAVE FOR ME TONIGHT.

00:34.034 --> 00:36.077
THIS STORY
WILL NEVER END.

00:36.077 --> 00:39.039
AS IF THIS LAST WEEK
HASN'T BEEN HARD ENOUGH,

00:39.039 --> 00:41.041
THE PRESS SEEMS TO HAVE
AN INSATIABLE APPETITE

00:41.041 --> 00:42.463
TO EVISCERATE ME.

00:42.463 --> 00:45.466
WELL, I'M DOING EVERYTHING I CAN
TO TELL YOUR SIDE.

00:45.466 --> 00:48.048
OHH, IT'S MERELY SCREAMING
IN THE WIND, MARGAUX.

00:48.048 --> 00:50.091
BUT I HATE SEEING YOU
ENDURE THESE ATTACKS.

00:50.091 --> 00:54.054
IT'S TOO HARD FOR ANYONE
TO BEAR, EVEN YOU.

00:54.054 --> 00:56.137
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]
 WHICH IS WHY SHE HAS ME.

00:56.137 --> 00:57.938
WHAT IS SHE DOING HERE?

00:57.938 --> 00:59.310
I INVITED HER.

00:59.310 --> 01:00.561
VICTORIA, I BEG YOU,

01:00.561 --> 01:02.773
DO NOT LET THAT WOMAN
INTO YOUR LIFE.

01:02.773 --> 01:05.025
WELL, SOMEONE HAS TO
LIGHTEN THE MOOD AROUND HERE.

01:05.025 --> 01:07.027
YOU'RE ABOUT AS DEPRESSING
AS A YANKEE GROOM

01:07.027 --> 01:08.189
AT A SOUTHERN WEDDING.

01:08.189 --> 01:10.191
YOU TRIED TO KILL ME,
YOU LUNATIC.

01:10.191 --> 01:12.993
OKAY, WHATEVER DID
OR DID NOT HAPPEN

01:12.993 --> 01:16.407
WAS DUE TO THE FACT THAT
MY FAMILY WAS DRUGGING ME.

01:16.407 --> 01:18.038
FORMER FAMILY.

01:18.038 --> 01:20.331
VICTORIA, PLEASE,
YOU DON'T NEED HER KIND OF HELP.

01:20.331 --> 01:21.832
OH,
THE HELL SHE DOESN'T.

01:21.832 --> 01:24.205
YOU HAVE HER HOLED UP IN HERE,
HIDING FROM THE WORLD.

01:24.205 --> 01:26.006
THAT IS NOT
HOW YOU HANDLE A SCANDAL.

01:26.006 --> 01:28.048
YOU FACE IT
WITH YOUR HEAD HELD HIGH.

01:28.048 --> 01:29.800
YOU DO NOT ACT LIKE
A GUILTY PERSON.

01:29.800 --> 01:31.472
OH, NO,
JUST LIKE A CRAZY ONE.

01:31.472 --> 01:33.053
STOP IT!

01:33.053 --> 01:35.266
IF I AM TO SURVIVE THIS,
I NEED BOTH OF YOU.

01:35.266 --> 01:37.017
NOW, CAN YOU DO THIS FOR ME
OR NOT?

01:37.017 --> 01:40.431
OH, VICTORIA, YOU KNOW
YOU WILL ALWAYS HAVE MY SUPPORT.

01:40.431 --> 01:42.102
THANK YOU.

01:44.024 --> 01:47.188
I'M SORRY ABOUT THAT.

01:47.188 --> 01:50.191
SOMETIMES, I JUST CAN'T
STOP MY LIPS FROM FLAPPING.

01:50.191 --> 01:52.363
DON'T WORRY ABOUT MARGAUX.
 [ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

01:52.363 --> 01:54.034
SHE DOESN'T UNDERSTAND
WHAT IT MEANS

01:54.034 --> 01:55.906
TO BE THE TARGET
OF UGLY HEADLINES.

01:55.906 --> 01:59.450
AND THAT'S A CLUB THAT BOTH
YOU AND I HAVE MEMBERSHIP TO.

01:59.450 --> 02:02.743
AND THE LAST ONE THAT WILL
EVER HAVE ME, I'M SURE.

02:02.743 --> 02:04.745
THAT DOESN'T SOUND LIKE
THE VICTORIA I KNOW.

02:04.745 --> 02:08.419
[ SIGHS ] LOUISE.
PERHAPS YOU'RE RIGHT.

02:08.419 --> 02:12.843
MAYBE I HAVE BEEN HIDDEN HERE
FOR TOO LONG.

02:12.843 --> 02:14.845
WOULD YOU PLEASE
TAKE ME TO LUNCH?

02:14.845 --> 02:18.058
OH,
WITH HEAD HELD HIGH.

02:53.093 --> 02:54.465
[ SIGHS ]

02:54.465 --> 02:56.887
I HEARD
YOU WERE DOING THIS.

02:56.887 --> 03:02.062
WANTED TO PAY MY RESPECTS,
BUT I-I DIDN'T WANT TO INTRUDE.

03:02.062 --> 03:05.226
I'M GLAD YOU'RE HERE.

03:05.226 --> 03:08.068
FOR HALF HER LIFE, YOU WERE
THE ONLY FAMILY AMANDA HAD --

03:08.068 --> 03:10.020
EMILY HAD.

03:10.020 --> 03:11.732
THAT'S GONNA
GET COMPLICATED.

03:11.732 --> 03:13.314
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:13.314 --> 03:16.076
YOU ALWAYS HAD A WAY
WITH UNDERSTATEMENTS.

03:18.158 --> 03:21.121
SO, STEVIE'S CHANGING
CARL'S BIRTH CERTIFICATE, TOO?

03:21.121 --> 03:22.743
YEAH, YEAH.

03:22.743 --> 03:26.747
ONCE MY MOM GETS AN IDEA IN HER
HEAD, THERE'S NO STOPPING HER.

03:26.747 --> 03:28.669
SHE AND YOUR DAD
ARE MEETING TODAY.

03:28.669 --> 03:29.920
YEAH, HE TOLD ME.

03:29.920 --> 03:33.504
I GUESS SHE NEEDS HIM
TO LEGALLY VERIFY THAT I'M ME.

03:33.504 --> 03:35.135
RIGHT.

03:35.135 --> 03:38.299
COMPLICATED.

03:38.299 --> 03:43.143
WELL...
IT'S ALL A GOOD THING.

03:43.143 --> 03:46.727
IT'S A CHANCE
TO START LIVING HONESTLY.

03:46.727 --> 03:49.189
WELL, YOU WERE ALWAYS
BETTER AT THAT THAN ME.

03:49.189 --> 03:51.191
MAYBE.

03:51.191 --> 03:54.355
BUT NOW THAT THIS IS OVER,
THERE'S NOTHING STOPPING YOU.

03:54.355 --> 03:58.198
[ SIGHS ]
 ALMOST OVER.

03:58.198 --> 04:01.662
VICTORIA STILL HAS THE DRIVE
WITH THE EVIDENCE ON ME.

04:01.662 --> 04:03.243
SHE HASN'T
MADE A MOVE YET,

04:03.243 --> 04:07.037
WHICH MEANS
SHE'S PLANNING SOMETHING.

04:07.037 --> 04:08.459
I HAVE NOLAN
TRACKING IT.

04:08.459 --> 04:09.870
[ SIGHS ]

04:09.870 --> 04:11.251
WELL, YOU GUYS
WILL FIGURE SOMETHING OUT.

04:11.251 --> 04:12.713
YOU ALWAYS DO.

04:12.713 --> 04:16.927
JACK.

04:16.927 --> 04:21.051
WHEN I GET THIS EVIDENCE BACK,
I'M DONE...FOR GOOD.

04:23.974 --> 04:25.556
[ SCOFFS ]

04:29.019 --> 04:30.811
THANKS FOR COMING
TODAY.

04:36.987 --> 04:38.989
[ SIGHS ]

04:38.989 --> 04:41.572
[ THE TALKING HEADS'
"BURNING DOWN THE HOUSE" PLAYS ]

04:41.572 --> 04:43.283
♪ WATCH OUT ♪

04:43.283 --> 04:46.076
♪ YOU MIGHT GET
WHAT YOU'RE AFTER ♪

04:46.076 --> 04:48.288
♪ COOL, BABY ♪

04:48.288 --> 04:50.290
♪ STRANGE BUT NOT A STRANGER ♪

04:50.290 --> 04:54.375
♪ I'M AN ORDINARY GUY ♪
 [ CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING ]

04:54.375 --> 04:58.679
♪ BURNING DOWN THE HOUSE ♪

04:58.679 --> 05:01.131
♪ HOLD TIGHT ♪

05:01.131 --> 05:03.474
♪ WAIT TILL THE PARTY'S OVER ♪

05:03.474 --> 05:05.265
♪ HOLD TIGHT ♪
 WHAT ABOUT THAT ONE?

05:05.265 --> 05:07.057
Tony:
NOT REALLY MY TYPE.

05:07.057 --> 05:09.930
THAT ONE
IS DEFINITELY MINE.

05:09.930 --> 05:13.143
COME ON, TONY. YOU COULD
TOTALLY ROCK AN ASAF GANOT.

05:13.143 --> 05:14.104
FIRST OFF,

05:14.104 --> 05:16.737
I CAN'T BELIEVE THAT
I'M SHOPPING AT A RUNWAY SHOW.

05:16.737 --> 05:18.108
AND, SECOND,
WHAT'S WRONG WITH MY SUIT?

05:18.108 --> 05:20.861
YOU HAVE TO KIND OF
TRUST ME ON THIS ONE.

05:20.861 --> 05:23.033
YOU'RE ALREADY SPONSORING
MY WORK'S CHARITY EVENT.

05:23.033 --> 05:24.244
THAT'S HUGE.

05:24.244 --> 05:25.446
AND IT'S MY PLEASURE.

05:25.446 --> 05:28.078
IF YOU WANT TO RAISE MONEY
IN THE HAMPTONS,

05:28.078 --> 05:30.751
YOU HAVE TO DRESS
THE PART, SIR.

05:30.751 --> 05:32.332
I JUST DON'T LIKE YOU
BUYING ME THINGS, NOLAN.

05:32.332 --> 05:35.085
OKAY -- OKAY. FINE.

05:35.085 --> 05:37.087
[ CHUCKLES ]
LOOK, WE WEAR THE SAME SIZE.

05:37.087 --> 05:39.009
I'LL BUY, YOU BORROW.

05:39.009 --> 05:40.130
[ LAUGHS ]

05:40.130 --> 05:42.222
TONY, YOUR WORK'S IMPORTANT,
AND, YOU KNOW,

05:42.222 --> 05:45.175
I WANT TO BE INVOLVED
IN SOME SMALL WAY IF I CAN.

05:45.175 --> 05:49.560
BESIDES, IT'S, UH --
IT'S NICE TO FEEL USEFUL.

05:49.560 --> 05:52.933
YOU HAVEN'T SMOOTHED THINGS OVER
WITH EMILY YET?

05:52.933 --> 05:55.315
I MEAN, UH...

05:55.315 --> 05:59.109
WE'VE TALKED SINCE OUR
LITTLE DUST-UP, BUT, UH...

05:59.109 --> 06:01.361
[ SIGHS ]

06:01.361 --> 06:05.195
...ONLY ABOUT STUFF, YOU KNOW,
THAT NEEDS TO BE HANDLED

06:05.195 --> 06:06.787
SINCE HER
COMING-OUT PARTY.

06:06.787 --> 06:09.159
EVERYTHING IS FIXABLE.

06:09.159 --> 06:10.621
THAT'S ACTUALLY DEBATABLE.
[ SCOFFS ]

06:10.621 --> 06:12.753
WHAT'S NOT DEBATABLE IS
THAT YOU GUYS ARE BEST FRIENDS

06:12.753 --> 06:14.294
WHO AREN'T TALKING
ABOUT ANYTHING REAL.

06:14.294 --> 06:15.916
YOU NEED TO
AIR THIS OUT.

06:15.916 --> 06:17.708
YOU SO DON'T KNOW EMS.

06:17.708 --> 06:20.170
SHE'S NOT A "SHARE HER FEELINGS"
KIND OF GIRL.

06:20.170 --> 06:24.004
THEN THERE'S THE PROBLEM.
AND I HATE SEEING YOU THIS WAY.

06:24.004 --> 06:26.176
YOU'RE A GREAT GUY
WITH A GOOD HEART,

06:26.176 --> 06:28.138
WHICH IS THE REAL REASON
I CAME TODAY.

06:28.138 --> 06:29.430
IT WASN'T FOR THE SUITS.

06:29.430 --> 06:31.642
♪ MY HOUSE
IS OUT OF THE ORDINARY ♪

06:31.642 --> 06:33.223
♪ THAT'S RIGHT ♪

06:33.223 --> 06:35.225
♪ DON'T WANT TO HURT NOBODY ♪

06:35.225 --> 06:36.857
♪ SOME THINGS ♪

06:36.857 --> 06:38.188
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

06:38.188 --> 06:41.021
YOU KNOW, BEFORE LUNCH,
WE SHOULD STOP AT TIFFANY'S.

06:41.021 --> 06:44.114
'CAUSE NOTHING CURES THE BLUES
LIKE A LITTLE BLUE BOX.

06:44.114 --> 06:45.696
THE CAR'S NOT HERE.

06:45.696 --> 06:48.118
OH, I'M SURE
THEY'RE JUST LATE.

06:48.118 --> 06:49.700
THIS WAS A MISTAKE.

06:49.700 --> 06:52.292
OH, NO, YOU'RE JUST
GETTING SPOOKED.

06:52.292 --> 06:55.125
LOUISE, WOULD YOU FIND THE CAR
FOR ME, PLEASE?

06:55.125 --> 06:56.416
SURE.

06:56.416 --> 06:59.089
BE BACK IN TWO SHAKES.

07:02.963 --> 07:04.885
[ TIRES SQUEAL IN DISTANCE ]

07:04.885 --> 07:06.136
[ HORN HONKS IN DISTANCE ]

07:11.602 --> 07:13.724
[ TIRES SQUEAL ]

07:13.724 --> 07:14.855
[ THUD ]

07:16.016 --> 07:18.108
[ THUD ]

07:18.108 --> 07:20.400
[ GASPS ]

07:20.400 --> 07:23.023
[ GROANS ]

07:23.023 --> 07:24.364
[ CAR APPROACHES ]

07:27.407 --> 07:28.779
[ GRUNTS ]

07:28.779 --> 07:30.491
Louise: VICTORIA!

07:30.491 --> 07:34.915
GET HER HELP!
CALL 911!

07:34.915 --> 07:38.418
OH, MY GOD!
VICTORIA! ARE YOU OKAY?!

07:38.418 --> 07:40.000
DID YOU SEE HIS FACE?

07:40.000 --> 07:41.381
[ GROANING ]

07:44.344 --> 07:46.136
WHAT IS IT?

07:48.218 --> 07:50.050
IT WAS EMILY.

08:06.697 --> 08:09.700
CALL ME RIGHT AWAY IF YOU HAVE
ANY DIZZINESS, MRS. GRAYSON.

08:09.700 --> 08:13.283
AND WATCH YOUR STEP.
THAT WAS A NASTY FALL YOU TOOK.

08:13.283 --> 08:15.285
WELL, THAT SEEMS TO BE
A RECURRING THEME FOR ME

08:15.285 --> 08:16.707
THESE DAYS, DOCTOR.

08:16.707 --> 08:18.709
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

08:18.709 --> 08:21.121
THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR YOUR HELP.

08:23.834 --> 08:27.007
[ SIGHS ]

08:27.007 --> 08:31.051
[ GROANS ]

08:31.051 --> 08:32.633
YOU DIDN'T TELL HIM
WHAT HAPPENED?

08:32.633 --> 08:35.345
I DON'T
WANT TO DISCUSS IT.

08:35.345 --> 08:37.558
BUT EMILY ATTACKED YOU.

08:37.558 --> 08:39.770
WE DON'T KNOW THAT
FOR SURE.

08:39.770 --> 08:42.522
I MAY HAVE BEEN
MISTAKEN EARLIER.

08:42.522 --> 08:44.314
IT'S THE ONLY THING
THAT MAKES SENSE.

08:44.314 --> 08:46.947
SHE'S TRYING TO STEAL BACK
THE EVIDENCE YOU HAVE.

08:46.947 --> 08:49.199
SHE DIDN'T GET IT,
DID SHE?
 NO.

08:49.199 --> 08:50.410
IT'S THE ONLY LEVERAGE
I HAVE LEFT.

08:50.410 --> 08:53.113
WELL, IT'S ONLY USEFUL
IF YOU USE IT.

08:53.113 --> 08:55.155
LOUISE,
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

08:55.155 --> 08:59.159
I KNOW WHAT SHE'S DONE TO YOU,
AND I KNOW YOU MUST BE SCARED.

08:59.159 --> 09:01.421
BUT THE POLICE
WILL BELIEVE YOU

09:01.421 --> 09:03.624
ONCE THEY SEE
WHAT'S ON THAT DRIVE.

09:03.624 --> 09:05.836
THE TRUTH IS ON YOUR SIDE,
VICTORIA.

09:05.836 --> 09:07.217
WHY WON'T
YOU USE JUST IT?

09:07.217 --> 09:09.429
[ WHIMPERS ]
SHE WANTS ME TO TRY TO USE IT

09:09.429 --> 09:10.841
SO SHE CAN TAKE IT
AWAY FROM ME.

09:10.841 --> 09:12.432
THAT'S WHAT SHE DOES.

09:12.432 --> 09:15.435
SHE MANIPULATES HER TARGETS
BEFORE THEY REALIZE IT,

09:15.435 --> 09:17.848
AND THEN IT'S TOO LATE.

09:17.848 --> 09:20.230
[ SIGHS ]

09:20.230 --> 09:23.233
SHE'S TAKEN EVERYTHING
AWAY FROM ME --

09:23.233 --> 09:28.488
MY SON...
HIS CHILD, CHARLOTTE.

09:28.488 --> 09:31.031
SHE WILL NOT STOP
UNTIL I'M DEAD,

09:31.031 --> 09:34.194
AND I REFUSE TO GIVE HER
THAT SATISFACTION.

09:34.194 --> 09:36.787
MARGAUX WAS RIGHT.

09:36.787 --> 09:39.579
I SHOULD NEVER
HAVE LEFT THIS ROOM.

09:39.579 --> 09:42.202
VICTORIA.

09:43.914 --> 09:45.916
JUST GO.

09:56.056 --> 09:57.638
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

09:57.638 --> 09:59.429
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

09:59.429 --> 10:01.852
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

10:04.775 --> 10:06.316
HEY.

10:06.316 --> 10:08.148
I KNEW YOU WERE OUT.

10:08.148 --> 10:09.730
JUST WANTED TO CHECK
YOUR SECURITY PROGRAM

10:09.730 --> 10:12.322
TO SEE IF WE LOCATED
THE DRIVE.

10:12.322 --> 10:14.534
WELL, VICTORIA HASN'T
PLUGGED IT IN IN THE LAST WEEK.

10:14.534 --> 10:17.738
WELL, GOOD NEWS --
SHE HASN'T PLAYED THAT CARD.

10:17.738 --> 10:22.162
BAD NEWS --
WE STILL DON'T KNOW WHERE IT IS.

10:22.162 --> 10:23.543
OKAY.

10:23.543 --> 10:27.207
WELL, I'M SORRY
TO INTRUDE.

10:27.207 --> 10:29.549
Nolan: GOOD TALK.

10:29.549 --> 10:31.171
WHAT DO YOU WANT ME
TO SAY, NOLAN?

10:31.171 --> 10:33.053
I DON'T KNOW. ANYTHING?

10:33.053 --> 10:34.174
I DON'T WANT TO FIGHT.

10:34.174 --> 10:36.216
I DON'T WANT TO FIGHT, EITHER,
BUT MAYBE WE SHOULD,

10:36.216 --> 10:38.098
BECAUSE THEN AT LEAST
I'D KNOW HOW YOU FEEL.

10:38.098 --> 10:41.892
YOU KEPT FILES WITHOUT TELLING
ME, AND NOW VICTORIA HAS THEM.

10:41.892 --> 10:44.474
THIS IS MY NIGHTMARE.
HOW DO YOU THINK I FEEL?

10:44.474 --> 10:47.728
I KNOW. I KNOW.

10:47.728 --> 10:50.110
I'M TERRIFIED THAT EVERYTHING
IS ABOUT TO COME UNDONE

10:50.110 --> 10:51.732
BECAUSE OF ME.

10:51.732 --> 10:54.945
AND TRUST ME, EMS,
THAT IS MY NIGHTMARE.

10:54.945 --> 11:00.620
BECAUSE...WELL, THIS HAS BEEN
THE BEST PART OF MY LIFE.

11:00.620 --> 11:03.623
THAT'S WHY
I HELD ONTO THAT STUFF.

11:03.623 --> 11:07.047
IT WAS MY INFINITY BOX.

11:07.047 --> 11:08.839
AND IT'S WHY
I STILL CALL YOU EMS

11:08.839 --> 11:11.421
EVEN THOUGH THE REST OF
THE WORLD KNOWS YOUR REAL NAME.

11:11.421 --> 11:14.424
[ SIGHS ]

11:14.424 --> 11:16.256
I HATE
THAT I FAILED YOU.

11:18.889 --> 11:21.221
I DON'T
WANT TO LOSE YOU.

11:21.221 --> 11:23.603
[ SIGHS ]

11:26.106 --> 11:27.267
[ SIGHS ]

11:27.267 --> 11:29.149
YOU KNOW, SOMETIMES,
I'M SO FOCUSED ON THE FIGHT,

11:29.149 --> 11:30.941
I DON'T SEE
WHAT'S RIGHT IN FRONT OF ME.

11:33.073 --> 11:34.444
I SHOULD HAVE SEEN
THAT YOU WERE HURTING, TOO.

11:34.444 --> 11:38.448
I MEAN, YEAH, I'M PISSED,
BUT YOU'RE NOT GONNA LOSE ME.

11:38.448 --> 11:41.081
WE'RE A TEAM.

11:41.081 --> 11:43.123
WE'RE GONNA GET THROUGH THIS,
'CAUSE THAT'S WHAT WE DO.

11:47.707 --> 11:50.380
NICE SUIT.

11:54.254 --> 11:56.256
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

12:02.142 --> 12:03.974
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]
 Stevie: DAVID.

12:03.974 --> 12:06.226
STEVIE.

12:06.226 --> 12:08.809
WE HAD AN APPOINTMENT, DAVID.
I WAITED AN HOUR.

12:08.809 --> 12:11.351
I CALLED TWICE.
WHAT HAPPENED?

12:11.351 --> 12:14.734
I GUESS MY, UH,
PHONE BATTERY MUST HAVE DIED.

12:14.734 --> 12:19.119
HMM. WELL,
I'M GLAD I TRACKED YOU DOWN.

12:19.119 --> 12:21.741
BEFORE I LEAVE TONIGHT,
I NEED ALL THE DOCUMENTATION

12:21.741 --> 12:25.325
REGARDING CARL'S
MOTHER'S NAME SIGNED.

12:25.325 --> 12:28.959
THERE'S A LOT OF DETAILS THAT
SUDDENLY NEED TO BE RECTIFIED

12:28.959 --> 12:30.130
IN LIGHT OF
YOUR DAUGHTER'S ANNOUNCEMENT.

12:30.130 --> 12:32.132
WAIT, IS THAT ANOTHER
ATTACK ON AMANDA?

12:32.132 --> 12:34.254
IT'S A LEGAL OBSERVATION.

12:34.254 --> 12:35.796
WELL,
I DON'T APPRECIATE IT.

12:35.796 --> 12:38.008
BELIEVE ME, DAVID, I DON'T
WANT TO SPEND MY LAST FEW HOURS

12:38.008 --> 12:39.139
IN TOWN
FIGHTING WITH YOU AGAIN.

12:39.139 --> 12:41.221
DON'T, THEN. JUST GO.

12:41.221 --> 12:42.762
THIS IS IMPORTANT.
 TO YOU.

12:42.762 --> 12:44.975
NOT EVERYTHING REVOLVES
AROUND STEVIE GRAYSON.

12:44.975 --> 12:47.187
WHERE IS THIS
COMING FROM?

12:47.187 --> 12:49.189
CARL HAS LOTS OF TIME
TO LEARN THE TRUTH.

12:49.189 --> 12:50.230
HELL, UP TO A YEAR AGO,
HE WOULD HAVE

12:50.230 --> 12:51.982
GOTTEN HIS OWN GRANDMOTHER'S
NAME WRONG.

12:51.982 --> 12:54.774
SO JUST DO US A FAVOR --
DROP IT.

12:54.774 --> 12:57.567
I DON'T KNOW WHAT'S CAUSING YOU
TO ACT LIKE THIS,

12:57.567 --> 12:59.319
BUT IT SURE AS HELL
ISN'T ME.

12:59.319 --> 13:02.612
RETURN THESE
BEFORE I LEAVE

13:02.612 --> 13:04.614
BUT AFTER YOU DEAL WITH
WHATEVER IT IS

13:04.614 --> 13:07.367
THAT'S MAKING YOU
ACT LIKE AN ASS.

13:12.002 --> 13:13.003
THIS IS GOOD TOGETHER.

13:13.003 --> 13:15.415
THAT ONE OVER THERE,
I THINK IT'S A MISTAKE.

13:15.415 --> 13:17.257
YES. THANK YOU.

13:21.091 --> 13:23.723
[ SPEAKING FRENCH ]

13:28.228 --> 13:30.640
I GOT YOUR MESSAGE.
YOU WANTED TO SEE ME?

13:30.640 --> 13:32.192
OH, FAR FROM IT,

13:32.192 --> 13:34.604
BUT VICTORIA'S
CURRENT SITUATION REQUIRES I DO.

13:34.604 --> 13:37.107
WHAT WILL IT TAKE
TO MAKE YOU GO AWAY?

13:37.107 --> 13:40.150
[ LAUGHS ]

13:40.150 --> 13:43.283
WELL, JUST A MINUTE, NOW.
YOU CAN'T BUY ME OFF.

13:43.283 --> 13:46.076
I DO NOT LIKE YOU,
I DO NOT TRUST YOU,

13:46.076 --> 13:48.118
AND I WILL DO
WHATEVER IT TAKES

13:48.118 --> 13:49.709
TO CUT YOU OUT
OF VICTORIA'S LIFE

13:49.709 --> 13:52.162
BEFORE YOUR RECKLESS BEHAVIOR
PUTS HER IN DANGER.

13:56.296 --> 13:58.128
WHAT HAPPENED?
TELL ME.

13:58.128 --> 14:00.380
[ SIGHS ]

14:00.380 --> 14:03.053
VICTORIA WAS ATTACKED
EARLIER.

14:03.053 --> 14:05.135
WELL,
SHE SAID NOTHING TO ME.

14:05.135 --> 14:07.227
WELL,
SHE'S PRETTY SHOOK UP.

14:07.227 --> 14:10.270
TRUTH BE TOLD, I FIGURED
THAT'S WHY YOU CALLED ME HERE.

14:10.270 --> 14:12.472
I THOUGHT YOU MIGHT BE
JUST AS CONCERNED AS I WAS.

14:12.472 --> 14:14.975
HOW DID THIS HAPPEN?
WHAT DID YOU DO?

14:14.975 --> 14:16.356
I THOUGHT I WAS HELPING.

14:16.356 --> 14:17.357
[ SIGHS ]

14:17.357 --> 14:19.189
IT WAS EMILY.

14:19.189 --> 14:22.072
SHE'S CLEARLY TRYING TO
STEAL BACK THAT DRIVE.

14:22.072 --> 14:23.153
[ SIGHS ]
 [ BEEP ]

14:23.153 --> 14:26.156
SIMONE: Yes, ma'am?
 SIMONE, CALL MY CAR.

14:26.156 --> 14:30.160
AND GET ME THE NUMBER OF THAT
AGENT AT THE FBI -- AGENT BAKER.

14:30.160 --> 14:31.791
VICTORIA SAID SHE DOESN'T
WANT TO INVOLVE THE FEDS.

14:31.791 --> 14:34.254
NO, I WILL DECIDE WHAT'S BEST
FOR HER FROM NOW ON.

14:34.254 --> 14:36.416
WELL,
WHAT CAN I DO TO HELP?

14:36.416 --> 14:38.548
STAY OUT OF MY WAY.

14:44.925 --> 14:46.096
[ CLICKING ]

14:46.096 --> 14:48.098
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

14:48.098 --> 14:49.509
BEN. HI

14:49.509 --> 14:51.101
DID YOU
HAVE A GOOD SWIM?

14:51.101 --> 14:53.513
UH, DID A LOOP
AROUND PENNFELD.

14:53.513 --> 14:55.775
LIGHTHOUSE?
THAT'S LIKE THREE MILES.

14:55.775 --> 14:57.147
[ SIGHS ]
HELPS ME FOCUS

14:57.147 --> 14:58.979
WHEN I'M DEALING
WITH A LOT OF THINGS.

14:58.979 --> 15:00.360
THREE MILES
IS A LOT OF THINGS.

15:00.360 --> 15:02.572
GIVEN WHAT WENT DOWN
WITH US,

15:02.572 --> 15:04.404
YOU DON'T THINK MAYBE
WE NEED TO TALK ABOUT IT?

15:04.404 --> 15:07.988
LOOK, BEN, YOU DON'T...KNOW
WHAT I'VE BEEN THROUGH,

15:07.988 --> 15:09.990
WHAT I'M GOING THROUGH.
 YOU'RE RIGHT. I DON'T.

15:09.990 --> 15:13.033
BUT I DO KNOW THAT I'VE PUT MY
CAREER AND MY LIFE ON THE LINE

15:13.033 --> 15:15.035
FOR YOU...

15:15.035 --> 15:18.418
BECAUSE FOR REASONS
THAT I CAN'T FATHOM RIGHT NOW,

15:18.418 --> 15:21.841
I REALLY LIKE YOU,
AND I WANT US TO WORK.

15:21.841 --> 15:24.254
BUT IF YOU DON'T,
JUST BE HONEST,

15:24.254 --> 15:25.925
'CAUSE I DON'T WANT TO BE
THAT GUY WITH YOU.

15:25.925 --> 15:27.137
NO, IT'S NOT THAT.

15:27.137 --> 15:31.181
LOOK, IT'S THAT I DON'T WANT TO
BE THAT GIRL WITH YOU.

15:31.181 --> 15:32.182
AND WHO'S THAT?

15:32.182 --> 15:33.183
SOMEONE WHO PUTS YOU
IN A POSITION

15:33.183 --> 15:35.015
WHERE YOU HAVE TO LIE
AGAIN,

15:35.015 --> 15:37.187
ESPECIALLY WHEN YOU'RE DOING THE
JOB YOU'VE ALWAYS WANTED TO DO.

15:37.187 --> 15:39.689
IT'S JUST --
IT'S NOT FAIR.

15:39.689 --> 15:42.192
WHY DON'T YOU LET ME DECIDE
WHAT'S RIGHT FOR ME?

15:42.192 --> 15:44.154
I NEED TO PUT ALL OF THIS
BEHIND ME FIRST.

15:44.154 --> 15:46.156
CAN YOU GIVE ME
A LITTLE MORE TIME?

15:48.158 --> 15:49.949
ALL YOU HAD TO DO
WAS ASK.

15:52.782 --> 15:54.574
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATING ]

15:54.574 --> 15:56.666
I'M GUESSING I DON'T WANT TO BE
HERE FOR THAT CALL.

15:56.666 --> 15:58.248
LOOK, WHY DON'T YOU
COME BACK LATER?

15:58.248 --> 15:59.919
WE'LL TALK MORE THEN,
OKAY?

16:04.544 --> 16:07.547
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

16:07.547 --> 16:09.139
NOLAN,
DO YOU HAVE SOMETHING?

16:09.139 --> 16:12.182
THINGS HAVE GOTTEN HARRY --
AS IN "S TRUMAN."

16:12.182 --> 16:14.514
They're about to
drop the big one.

16:14.514 --> 16:17.727
I INTERCEPTED A PHONE CALL
BETWEEN MARGAUX AND VICTORIA.

16:17.727 --> 16:19.399
THEY'RE USING
THE EVIDENCE.

16:19.399 --> 16:23.063
The Feds are on their way
to Victoria's hotel.

16:23.063 --> 16:24.774
IT'S GOING DOWN NOW.

16:30.990 --> 16:33.243
MARGAUX ARRANGED FOR THE FBI
TO QUESTION VICTORIA

16:33.243 --> 16:34.244
AT THE PENTHOUSE.

16:34.244 --> 16:36.286
IT'S A SMART MOVE
ON HER PART --

16:36.286 --> 16:37.997
NO CHANCE FOR US
TO INTERCEPT THEM,

16:37.997 --> 16:39.879
AND SHE KNOWS
THAT WE DON'T HAVE ENOUGH TIME

16:39.879 --> 16:42.082
TO PULL OFF AN "EMILY'S ELEVEN"
AND BREAK INTO THE SUITE.

16:42.082 --> 16:43.503
VICTORIA WON'T LET THE DRIVE
OUT OF HER SIGHT

16:43.503 --> 16:45.335
LONG ENOUGH FOR US TO TAKE IT,
ANYWAY.

16:45.335 --> 16:47.127
YEAH, BUT WE HAVE TO.

16:47.127 --> 16:49.759
I MEAN, IT'S NOT LIKE BEFORE.
WE CAN'T ERASE IT REMOTELY.

16:49.759 --> 16:51.511
AND, EM, IF THE FEDS GET THEIR
HANDS ON THIS EVIDENCE, IT --

16:51.511 --> 16:53.433
WE'RE NOT GONNA
LET THAT HAPPEN, REMEMBER?

16:55.014 --> 16:56.096
IS THAT WHAT I ASKED FOR?

16:56.096 --> 16:59.939
YEAH, GRAPHITE SCANNER,
LIKE THE ONES AIRPORTS USE

16:59.939 --> 17:04.144
TO SEARCH
FOR CHEMICAL EXPLOSIVES.

17:04.144 --> 17:06.986
I MODIFIED IT TO SEARCH
FOR THE COATING AGENTS

17:06.986 --> 17:09.148
USED ON THUMB-DRIVE
ACTUATORS.

17:10.150 --> 17:11.651
GOOD.
I BETTER GET MOVING.

17:11.651 --> 17:12.992
I GUESS I'LL CALL TONY

17:12.992 --> 17:15.454
AND, UH, TELL HIM I CAN'T
MAKE IT TO THE CHARITY EVENT.

17:15.454 --> 17:16.826
NO. I'LL HANDLE IT.

17:18.208 --> 17:20.869
[ SIGHS ]
I DIDN'T MEAN IT LIKE THAT.

17:20.869 --> 17:25.875
LOOK, THE PAST FEW YEARS,
THIS HAS BEEN OUR LIFE.

17:25.875 --> 17:28.258
WHETHER WE WANT TO ADMIT IT
OR NOT,

17:28.258 --> 17:30.260
IT'S BEEN EASIER
TO FOCUS ON THE MISSION

17:30.260 --> 17:33.593
THAN TO THINK ABOUT
WHAT COMES NEXT.

17:33.593 --> 17:35.595
YEAH, YOU'RE RIGHT.

17:35.595 --> 17:38.518
[ CHUCKLES ]
I HATE IMAGINING LIFE AFTER EMS.

17:38.518 --> 17:40.310
YOU DON'T HAVE TO.

17:40.310 --> 17:42.482
THERE'S ALWAYS GONNA BE
A "NOLAN AND EMILY."

17:42.482 --> 17:45.064
BUT "NOLAN AND TONY"
MIGHT NOT HAVE A CHANCE

17:45.064 --> 17:49.068
IF YOU STAND HIM UP TODAY,
AND I'D HATE TO SEE THAT HAPPEN.

17:49.068 --> 17:51.951
I HEAR
HE'S A REALLY GREAT GUY.

17:53.743 --> 17:55.535
GO FINISH THIS, EMS.

18:02.912 --> 18:05.505
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

18:05.505 --> 18:08.128
YOU NEVER STOP WORKING.

18:08.128 --> 18:09.879
NOT WHEN THERE'S WORK
TO BE DONE.

18:09.879 --> 18:12.262
LISTEN, I, UH...
ABOUT THAT --

18:12.262 --> 18:14.474
I BROUGHT THE PAPERS
AND AN APOLOGY.

18:14.474 --> 18:17.347
YOU WERE RIGHT.
IT WASN'T ABOUT YOU.

18:17.347 --> 18:18.848
I'M SORRY.

18:18.848 --> 18:21.641
APPRECIATE IT.

18:24.984 --> 18:29.068
DESPITE MY REPUTATION,
I DO KNOW HOW TO LISTEN.

18:29.068 --> 18:31.281
WANT TO TALK ABOUT IT?

18:34.033 --> 18:36.196
UH...

18:38.658 --> 18:43.082
IT STARTED THAT DAY, UH,
ON THE BOAT, WHEN I CUT MY HAND.

18:43.082 --> 18:45.084
AT THE HOSPITAL,
THEY RAN MY BLOOD WORK.

18:45.084 --> 18:48.087
"IT'S A NORMAL PROCEDURE,"
THEY SAID.

18:48.087 --> 18:52.252
THE TESTS, UH,
THEY CAME BACK ABNORMAL.

18:52.252 --> 18:54.634
IT'S LYMPHOMA.

18:54.634 --> 18:58.218
OH, DAVID, I'M...

18:58.218 --> 18:59.599
I'M SO SORRY.

18:59.599 --> 19:01.261
DO THEY KNOW --

19:01.261 --> 19:03.683
THE PROGNOSIS? UH...

19:03.683 --> 19:09.439
THEY SAID THEY GOT IT IN TIME,
THAT THEY WANT TO BE AGGRESSIVE.

19:09.439 --> 19:11.481
I START CHEMO TONIGHT.

19:11.481 --> 19:15.535
LOOKS LIKE THAT FIGHT WE HAD
WAS A BLESSING IN DISGUISE.

19:15.535 --> 19:17.657
HOW'S YOUR DAUGHTER
TAKING IT?

19:19.199 --> 19:21.491
YOU HAVEN'T TOLD HER.

19:21.491 --> 19:24.043
IT WAS ONLY CONFIRMED
THIS MORNING.

19:24.043 --> 19:26.165
THAT'S WHY I WAS IN NO STATE
TO MAKE OUR MEETING.

19:26.165 --> 19:30.129
I'M GONNA TELL AMANDA
LATER.

19:30.129 --> 19:33.793
I-I JUST -- I DON'T KNOW
HOW SHE'S GONNA TAKE IT.

19:33.793 --> 19:37.217
I WOULDN'T WORRY
ABOUT IT TOO MUCH.

19:37.217 --> 19:39.679
YOU HAVE THE TOUGHEST KID
ON THE BLOCK.

19:42.352 --> 19:44.514
Margaux:
EMILY THORNE IS NO HERO.

19:44.514 --> 19:47.477
SHE IS A CRIMINAL
WHO THINKS SHE'S ABOVE THE LAW.

19:47.477 --> 19:49.899
WHEN YOU SAY "EMILY THORNE," YOU
MEAN "AMANDA CLARKE," CORRECT?

19:49.899 --> 19:51.981
BY ANY NAME,
SHE IS A DANGEROUS WOMAN.

19:51.981 --> 19:53.903
SHE ATTACKED VICTORIA
THIS MORNING.

19:53.903 --> 19:55.024
UH, SO YOU SAID
ON THE PHONE.

19:55.024 --> 19:56.155
BUT WHEN I CHECKED
WITH THE DOCTOR,

19:56.155 --> 19:57.907
HE TOLD ME THAT MRS. GRAYSON
CLAIMED SHE FELL.

19:57.907 --> 19:59.118
WELL,
THAT WAS A COVER STORY

19:59.118 --> 20:01.080
TO PROTECT HERSELF
FROM RETALIATION.

20:01.080 --> 20:04.123
EMILY IS A COMPULSIVE WOMAN.
SHE TAPPED PHONES.

20:04.123 --> 20:06.376
SHE POSED AS
A HOMELAND SECURITY AGENT.

20:06.376 --> 20:10.209
SHE THREATENED MY FATHER,
AND NOW HE'S DEAD BECAUSE OF IT.

20:10.209 --> 20:13.132
WE CANNOT LET HER
GO ON TORTURING US LIKE THIS.

20:13.132 --> 20:15.094
MRS. GRAYSON, YOU PROVIDED
VITAL EVIDENCE TO THE BUREAU

20:15.094 --> 20:17.006
AGAINST YOUR EX-HUSBAND
IN THE PAST.

20:17.006 --> 20:19.138
THAT'S WHY I'M TAKING THIS
AS SERIOUSLY AS I AM RIGHT NOW.

20:19.138 --> 20:21.841
BUT I CAN'T HELP YOU
IF YOU REFUSE TO COOPERATE.

20:21.841 --> 20:25.645
VICTORIA, WE CAN END THIS.
SHOW HIM THE EVIDENCE.

20:25.645 --> 20:26.766
[ ALARM BLARING ]

20:26.766 --> 20:28.398
THAT'S THE FIRE ALARM.
WE NEED TO EVACUATE.

20:28.398 --> 20:30.189
NO, THERE IS NO FIRE.
THIS IS EMILY.

20:30.189 --> 20:32.272
SHE WANTS US
OUT OF THIS ROOM.

20:32.272 --> 20:34.153
YOU THINK I'M LETTING YOU STAY
UP HERE BASED ON YOUR HUNCH?

20:34.153 --> 20:35.775
HERE.

20:35.775 --> 20:38.408
HOLD ONTO IT,
AND DON'T LET ANYBODY NEAR YOU.

20:42.362 --> 20:44.203
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

20:44.203 --> 20:45.705
LET'S GO, LADIES.

20:45.705 --> 20:47.707
[ BLARING CONTINUES ]

20:49.829 --> 20:51.831
[ RADIO CHATTER ]

20:57.176 --> 21:01.641
COME ON. WE NEED TO
KEEP MOVING. LET'S GO.

21:03.843 --> 21:05.845
I DON'T LIKE BEING
OUT IN THE OPEN, AGENT BAKER.

21:05.845 --> 21:08.227
SHE CAN GET TO US HERE.
 LOOK, CALM DOWN,
MRS. GRAYSON.

21:08.227 --> 21:10.810
I CAN ASSURE YOU
I HAVE NOT SEEN HER.

21:10.810 --> 21:11.981
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

21:11.981 --> 21:13.353
SHE WILL TAKE THE EVIDENCE
AWAY FROM YOU.

21:13.353 --> 21:15.194
I HAVE IT RIGHT HERE.

21:18.067 --> 21:19.699
IT'S GONE, ISN'T IT?

21:19.699 --> 21:21.110
UH, I MUST HAVE DROPPED IT
IN THE STAIRWELL.

21:21.110 --> 21:22.402
NO,
YOU DIDN'T DROP IT.

21:22.402 --> 21:23.823
IT WAS AMANDA CLARKE, AND
WE PLAYED RIGHT INTO HER HANDS!

21:23.823 --> 21:24.994
SHE TOOK THE EVIDENCE!
SHE TOOK IT!

21:24.994 --> 21:27.206
S-S-SHE KNEW YOU WERE COMING.
SHE TAPPED MY PHONES.

21:27.206 --> 21:29.208
SHE SET OFF THE ALARM.
D-DON'T YOU GET IT?

21:29.208 --> 21:32.081
AMANDA CLARKE IS HERE.
PLEASE, YOU GOT TO FIND HER.

21:32.081 --> 21:33.252
YOU GOT TO FIND HER.

21:33.252 --> 21:34.674
Margaux: IT'S OKAY.
 SHE'S HERE!

21:34.674 --> 21:36.255
DON'T LET HER GET AWAY!

21:36.255 --> 21:37.256
VICTORIA.
 WHAT?

21:37.256 --> 21:40.380
WE'LL FIND HER.

21:51.481 --> 21:53.142
HEY.

21:53.142 --> 21:55.935
AH, AMANDA.
THANKS FOR COMING.

21:55.935 --> 21:59.108
I WANTED TO TALK
TO YOU.

21:59.108 --> 22:02.402
WAIT.

22:02.402 --> 22:05.074
SOMETHING IS DIFFERENT.
WHAT IS IT?

22:05.074 --> 22:08.077
[ Sighing ] IT'S OVER.

22:08.077 --> 22:09.288
WHAT IS?

22:09.288 --> 22:12.712
EVERYTHING --
THIS WHOLE DAMN WAR.

22:12.712 --> 22:16.085
[ SIGHS ]

22:16.085 --> 22:20.510
VICTORIA WAS
GONNA USE THIS TODAY --

22:20.510 --> 22:23.012
THE LAST PIECE OF LEVERAGE
SHE HAD ON ME.

22:26.055 --> 22:28.428
[ THUMB DRIVE SNAPS ]
 [ SIGHS ]

22:31.891 --> 22:33.643
[ SIGHS ]

22:33.643 --> 22:36.646
YOU KNOW
WHAT THIS MEANS?

22:36.646 --> 22:38.648
FINISHING THIS
ISN'T JUST A FANTASY.

22:38.648 --> 22:41.821
IT HAPPENED -- TODAY.
I...

22:41.821 --> 22:45.194
FOR THE FIRST TIME
IN MY LIFE,

22:45.194 --> 22:47.366
THERE ARE NO MORE BATTLES
TO FIGHT.

22:49.579 --> 22:51.581
[ LAUGHS ]

22:53.873 --> 22:55.875
[ CHUCKLES ]

22:55.875 --> 22:58.878
YOU WANTED TO
TALK TO ME?

22:58.878 --> 23:00.339
YEAH.

23:00.339 --> 23:03.342
I, UM, WANTED TO TELL YOU
I LOVED YOU

23:03.342 --> 23:07.346
AND THAT, UM...

23:07.346 --> 23:10.970
I AM SO VERY PROUD OF YOU,
AMANDA.

23:10.970 --> 23:13.142
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:13.142 --> 23:15.144
[ SMOOCHES ]

23:20.820 --> 23:24.403
IT'S A WONDERFUL EVENT,
MR. ROSS.
 CHEERS.

23:24.403 --> 23:27.827
WHAT INSPIRED YOU TO DO THIS
FOR MY STAR EMPLOYEE TODAY?

23:27.827 --> 23:31.991
ACTUALLY...I NEVER REALLY HAD
A RELATIONSHIP WITH MY FATHER --

23:31.991 --> 23:33.162
NOT A GOOD ONE, ANYWAY.

23:33.162 --> 23:35.795
AND AS A RESULT,
I GREW UP AN ANGRY YOUNG MAN

23:35.795 --> 23:37.376
WHO HAD HIS FAIR SHARE
OF PROBLEMS,

23:37.376 --> 23:39.799
MADE MISTAKES,
AND, UH...

23:39.799 --> 23:42.882
UNTIL I MET SOMEBODY WHO FINALLY
DECIDED TO BELIEVE IN ME.

23:42.882 --> 23:44.844
DAVID CLARKE --
I'VE HEARD YOU SPEAK ABOUT HIM.

23:44.844 --> 23:48.047
CHANGED MY LIFE,
MUCH LIKE YOUR PROGRAM MUST DO

23:48.047 --> 23:51.601
FOR KIDS FACING SIMILAR
SITUATIONS, PROBLEMS.

23:51.601 --> 23:53.603
UH, THAT'S WHY I DECIDED
TO HOST THIS EVENT.

23:53.603 --> 23:56.225
TONY.
 AND WE'RE VERY GRATEFUL
FOR THAT.

23:56.225 --> 23:57.607
AND HOW DID YOU TWO
COME TO MEET?

23:57.607 --> 23:59.649
Louise:
OH, JUICY QUESTION.

23:59.649 --> 24:01.320
YOU WANT TO FIELD IT,
OR SHOULD I?

24:01.320 --> 24:03.322
LOUISE.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

24:03.322 --> 24:05.324
OH, I'M JUST CONTRIBUTING
TO THE CONVERSATION.

24:05.324 --> 24:08.117
MY EX-HUSBAND HERE DOES WEAVE
SUCH DELIGHTFUL TALES,

24:08.117 --> 24:09.448
DOESN'T HE?

24:09.448 --> 24:12.281
BUT I HAVE TO WARN YOU,
THEY ARE MORE FICTION THAN FACT.

24:12.281 --> 24:14.534
AND YOU WILL HAVE TO
EXCUSE MY EX-WIFE.

24:14.534 --> 24:16.125
SHE HELD SO MUCH PROMISE...

24:16.125 --> 24:17.166
ONCE.
 OH.

24:18.167 --> 24:19.168
WHAT ARE YOU AFTER?
 YOU.

24:19.168 --> 24:20.790
NOW, WE CAN
DO THIS RIGHT HERE

24:20.790 --> 24:23.212
IN FRONT OF
YOUR NEW PARAMOUR'S EMPLOYER,

24:23.212 --> 24:26.005
OR WE COULD GO SOMEPLACE PRIVATE
AND HAVE A FRANK CONVERSATION.

24:26.005 --> 24:28.638
YOU, ME, OUTSIDE, FIVE MINUTES.
DO NOT MAKE A SCENE.

24:28.638 --> 24:31.140
NOW,
WHY WOULD I EVER DO THAT?

24:31.140 --> 24:34.053
OH, NO, CLUMSY ME.

24:34.053 --> 24:38.858
AND ALL OVER
YOUR BRAND-NEW ASAF GANOT SUIT,

24:38.858 --> 24:40.810
WHICH COSTS MORE THAN
THE DONATION I MADE

24:40.810 --> 24:42.401
TO YOUR FOUNDATION
EARLIER TODAY.

24:42.401 --> 24:45.024
YOU KNOW, SOCIAL WORK
MUST BE MUCH MORE LUCRATIVE

24:45.024 --> 24:46.445
THAN I WAS LED TO BELIEVE.

24:46.445 --> 24:48.027
L-LOUISE, STOP IT.

24:48.027 --> 24:52.872
UNLESS...YOUR FOUNDATION
WASN'T THE SOLE BENEFICIARY

24:52.872 --> 24:55.615
OF MY EX-HUSBAND'S
CHARITY.

24:55.615 --> 24:57.827
[ CHUCKLES ]
WELL, NOW I SEE WHY

24:57.827 --> 25:00.079
YOU WERE SO INTENT
ON GETTING A QUICKIE DIVORCE.

25:00.079 --> 25:02.381
GOOD ON YOU.

25:02.381 --> 25:04.714
WRECK A MARRIAGE,
GET A SUGAR DADDY.

25:04.714 --> 25:06.085
Tony:
NOW, THAT'S NOT TRUE.

25:08.217 --> 25:10.219
[ SCOFFS ]
I'M SO SORRY.

25:10.219 --> 25:11.551
EXCUSE ME. I'M SORRY.

25:11.551 --> 25:13.553
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

25:18.638 --> 25:20.600
YOU KNOW, I DIDN'T THINK
THAT YOU WERE A LOST CAUSE

25:20.600 --> 25:21.811
UNTIL RIGHT NOW.

25:21.811 --> 25:23.402
TONY WAS AN INNOCENT
IN ALL THIS.

25:23.402 --> 25:24.814
HOW COULD YOU DO THAT
TO HIM?

25:24.814 --> 25:26.986
YOU HURT MY FRIENDS,
I HURT YOURS.

25:26.986 --> 25:29.408
OH, LISTEN TO YOU --
CONSIDERING VICTORIA A FRIEND

25:29.408 --> 25:31.150
AND TAKING A PAGE
OUT OF HER PLAYBOOK?

25:31.150 --> 25:33.532
MM, MORE LIKE EMILY,
IF YOU ASK ME.

25:33.532 --> 25:35.114
HEY, SHE NEVER WENT AFTER
ANYBODY THAT DID NOT DESERVE IT.

25:35.114 --> 25:37.036
OH,
DON'T ROMANTICIZE HER!

25:37.036 --> 25:38.367
SHE GETS OFF
ON TORTURING VICTORIA,

25:38.367 --> 25:40.119
JUST LIKE SHE DID TODAY
IN THAT GARAGE.

25:40.119 --> 25:42.962
I HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

25:42.962 --> 25:44.163
OH, MORE LIES!

25:44.163 --> 25:46.125
I KNOW YOU HELPED HER
STEAL THAT DRIVE BACK,

25:46.125 --> 25:48.377
AND I KNOW THAT THIS CHARADE
OF AN EVENT IS YOUR ALIBI.

25:48.377 --> 25:53.172
PLAUSIBLE DENIABILITY WHILE
EMILY DOES HER DIRTY WORK.

25:53.172 --> 25:57.176
OH, WOW, YOU'RE GOOD,
EXCEPT FOR THOSE PESKY DETAILS.

25:57.176 --> 25:58.598
OH, DON'T STAND THERE
AND PLAY DUMB.

25:58.598 --> 26:01.230
YOU ARE KICKING VICTORIA
WHILE SHE'S DOWN.

26:01.230 --> 26:02.982
WHAT DO YOU THINK
THAT WILL DO TO HER?

26:02.982 --> 26:07.066
WHY DON'T YOU JUST BE A MAN
AND ADMIT TO WHAT YOU'VE DONE?

26:07.066 --> 26:09.859
LOUISE, YOU'RE IN
OVER YOUR HEAD,

26:09.859 --> 26:11.400
AND YOU PICKED
THE WRONG SIDE.

26:11.400 --> 26:13.613
OH, UM, AND WHILE
YOU WERE TRYING TO

26:13.613 --> 26:16.786
RECORD A CONFESSION
ON YOUR PHONE RIGHT NOW,

26:16.786 --> 26:19.999
I WAS RUNNING AN APP THAT
RESET IT TO FACTORY SETTINGS.

26:19.999 --> 26:24.163
LIKE I SAID --
YOU, HEAD, OVER.

26:24.163 --> 26:25.544
[ WHISTLES ]

26:31.841 --> 26:34.053
[ SIGHS ]

26:34.053 --> 26:35.214
[ CHUCKLES ]
 UP THE HILL.

26:35.214 --> 26:37.637
YOU WANT ME
TO DO THIS SIDE?

26:37.637 --> 26:39.218
HERE WE GO.
HERE WE GO.

26:39.218 --> 26:40.429
HEY.

26:40.429 --> 26:42.061
HEY.

26:42.061 --> 26:43.432
THIS GOES UP.
 CHOO-CHOO!

26:43.432 --> 26:45.144
AH.
 LOOK HERE.

26:45.144 --> 26:48.187
[ GASPS ] CHOO-CHOO! UH-OH!
 ALL THIS JUST TO CHANGE
A MOTHER'S NAME, HUH?

26:48.187 --> 26:49.779
YOU'RE LUCKY YOU GET
THE FAMILY DISCOUNT.

26:49.779 --> 26:51.861
I USUALLY CHARGE
BY THE POUND.

26:51.861 --> 26:53.442
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:53.442 --> 26:55.865
WELL, THANKS FOR TAKING CARE
OF ALL THIS.

26:55.865 --> 26:57.036
MM-HMM.

26:57.036 --> 26:57.997
[ SIGHS ]

26:57.997 --> 27:00.159
MAYBE I SHOULD
STICK AROUND.

27:00.159 --> 27:02.241
OH, YOU DON'T NEED TO WORRY
ABOUT ME.

27:02.241 --> 27:04.083
IT'S NOT WORRY.
I JUST...

27:04.083 --> 27:05.454
[ BABBLES ]

27:05.454 --> 27:07.246
[ CHUCKLES ]

27:07.246 --> 27:09.799
...I REALLY TREASURE THIS TIME
WITH YOU AND CARL,

27:09.799 --> 27:11.921
AND I'VE MISSED
SO MUCH.

27:11.921 --> 27:12.922
MISSED.
[ BABBLES ]

27:12.922 --> 27:14.463
I'M NOT GONNA BE AROUND
FOREVER.

27:14.463 --> 27:17.096
LET ME SEE.

27:17.096 --> 27:21.260
OH, NOT AGAIN.
CHOO-CHOO.

27:21.260 --> 27:23.102
WHERE'S THIS
COMING FROM?

27:25.725 --> 27:27.977
I GUESS
I JUST HATE GOODBYES.
 [ BABBLING ]

27:27.977 --> 27:30.109
WELL, YEAH, SO DO I.

27:30.109 --> 27:33.943
SO I GET TO BE AN ANNOYING
MOTHER FOR ANOTHER FEW HOURS.

27:33.943 --> 27:36.946
HERE.

27:36.946 --> 27:40.579
WHAT'S NEXT?
YOU QUIT THE FORCE.

27:40.579 --> 27:43.122
YOU CAN'T WORK
AT THAT CLUB FOREVER.

27:43.122 --> 27:45.084
YOU KNOW
WHAT YOU WANT?

27:45.084 --> 27:49.088
[ SIGHS ]
ACTUALLY, YEAH.

27:50.710 --> 27:54.503
FOR THE FIRST TIME IN A WHILE,
I THINK I DO.

27:54.503 --> 27:58.718
DON'T WORRY, MARGAUX.
I'LL BE FINE.

27:58.718 --> 28:01.560
Margaux: YOU SHOULDN'T WAIT
FOR YOUR BODYGUARD ALONE.

28:02.852 --> 28:06.305
[ CHUCKLES ]
COME HERE.

28:07.937 --> 28:10.569
DON'T WORRY ABOUT ME
SO MUCH.

28:10.569 --> 28:12.571
HMM?

28:20.119 --> 28:23.162
I TRUST YOU WERE ABLE TO GET
WHAT I WAS ASKING FOR?

28:23.162 --> 28:24.744
YES, MA'AM.

28:24.744 --> 28:27.166
SHE WAS DEFINITELY
OF A MIND-SET TO SELL, TOO.

28:27.166 --> 28:29.328
WELL,
OF COURSE SHE WAS.

28:29.328 --> 28:34.173
IT LOST ITS APPEAL DUE TO
EMILY'S TELEVISED ASSASSINATION.

28:34.173 --> 28:37.336
YOU MIND ME ASKING WHY GETTING
THIS WAS SO IMPORTANT TO YOU?

28:41.180 --> 28:43.973
IT'S A MEMENTO...

28:43.973 --> 28:46.105
OF A BYGONE ERA.

28:47.436 --> 28:48.647
[ SIGHS ]

28:52.061 --> 28:55.654
THIS IS WAY MORE
THAN WE AGREED TO.

28:55.654 --> 28:57.857
THAT'S BECAUSE WE WON'T BE
SEEING EACH OTHER AGAIN,

28:57.857 --> 28:59.158
MR. RENNER.

28:59.158 --> 29:01.660
MRS. GRAYSON,
WHAT DO YOU PLAN TO DO?

29:01.660 --> 29:03.452
SOMETHING
AMANDA CLARKE

29:03.452 --> 29:07.456
NEVER HAD THE COURAGE
TO DO HERSELF --

29:07.456 --> 29:09.578
END THIS.

29:15.254 --> 29:17.466
[ SIGHS ]

29:17.466 --> 29:20.469
DO YOU WANT ANOTHER DRINK?
'CAUSE I WANT 12.

29:20.469 --> 29:22.051
[ CHUCKLES ]

29:22.051 --> 29:24.013
PARTY DIDN'T GO
LIKE YOU PLANNED?

29:24.013 --> 29:25.344
WHY DO WE EVEN
STILL THROW THEM?

29:25.344 --> 29:28.347
NO, NO, NO, SERIOUSLY.
NO LEARNING CURVE.

29:28.347 --> 29:31.730
I MEAN, I JUST WATCHED TONY
LEAVE WITH HIS BOSS,

29:31.730 --> 29:35.604
WHO WAS NOT HAPPY,
SO...THAT'S OVER.

29:35.604 --> 29:38.737
WHERE IS MY BARKEEP?

29:38.737 --> 29:41.200
I HAVE SORROWS TO DROWN.
MIGUEL!

29:41.200 --> 29:44.113
I ASKED MIGUEL
TO GRAB MY LAST PAYCHECK.

29:44.113 --> 29:48.407
SORRY TO SEE YOU GO, JACK.
STAY IN TOUCH.

29:48.407 --> 29:49.829
Jack:
ABSOLUTELY. THANK YOU.

29:49.829 --> 29:51.000
LAST PAYCHECK?

29:51.000 --> 29:53.412
AFTER ALL THE TROUBLE I WENT TO
SETTING UP THAT DAYCARE,

29:53.412 --> 29:55.504
IT WOULD HAVE BEEN NICE TO GET
TWO WEEKS' NOTICE, MY FRIEND.

29:55.504 --> 29:57.917
THAT'S ACTUALLY
WHY I'M HERE.

29:57.917 --> 30:02.551
I'M NOT JUST QUITTING, NOLAN.
I'M...I'M LEAVING.

30:02.551 --> 30:05.054
OKAY.
W-WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

30:05.054 --> 30:08.057
LOS ANGELES.
I'M...TAKING CARL TONIGHT.

30:08.057 --> 30:10.269
AND ONCE WE GET SET UP THERE,
I'M SELLING THE HOUSE HERE.

30:10.269 --> 30:12.641
I'M GONNA START FRESH.

30:12.641 --> 30:16.105
WAIT. I --
H-HAVE YOU TALKED TO EMILY?

30:16.105 --> 30:19.738
THERE'S NOTHING
LEFT TO SAY, NOLAN.

30:19.738 --> 30:21.530
[ SCOFFS ]
I TOLD HER HOW I FELT.

30:21.530 --> 30:22.942
SHE MADE IT CLEAR
SHE DIDN'T WANT TO BE WITH ME.

30:22.942 --> 30:24.323
LOOK,
IT'S TIME I FACED REALITY.

30:24.323 --> 30:26.615
SHE NEVER WANTED ME
TO BE A PART OF THIS, ANYWAY.

30:26.615 --> 30:28.998
ONLY BECAUSE
SHE WAS PROTECTING YOU.

30:28.998 --> 30:31.210
SHE LOVES YOU, JACK.
 [ CHUCKLES ]

30:31.210 --> 30:33.412
I CAN'T HEAR THAT
RIGHT NOW.

30:35.044 --> 30:37.046
AND I CERTAINLY
DIDN'T HEAR IT FROM HER.

30:37.046 --> 30:40.880
WE BOTH KNOW THAT WHAT
EMILY SAYS AND WHAT EMILY FEELS

30:40.880 --> 30:42.631
ARE TWO
VERY DIFFERENT THINGS.

30:42.631 --> 30:43.632
YES, WE DO.

30:43.632 --> 30:45.424
BUT THIS MORNING
AT THE CEMETERY,

30:45.424 --> 30:47.226
I REALIZED SOMETHING ELSE.

30:47.226 --> 30:50.059
EMILY'S
NEVER GONNA STOP.

30:50.059 --> 30:51.640
SHE CAN'T.

30:51.640 --> 30:54.603
THIS LIFE,
IT'S ALL SHE'S KNOWN.

30:54.603 --> 30:56.976
AND, YOU KNOW, MAYBE IT --
MAYBE IT STARTED OUT

30:56.976 --> 30:59.028
AS SOME WAY
TO KEEP HER FATHER ALIVE

30:59.028 --> 31:01.190
WHEN SHE THOUGHT
SHE'D LOST HIM,

31:01.190 --> 31:02.982
BUT IT'S TURNED
INTO SOMETHING ELSE,

31:02.982 --> 31:07.076
SOMETHING THAT SHE EITHER
CAN'T LET GO OF...

31:07.076 --> 31:08.747
OR DOESN'T WANT TO.

31:08.747 --> 31:11.951
DON'T DO THIS, JACK.

31:11.951 --> 31:13.542
PLEASE.

31:13.542 --> 31:16.755
LOOK, THINGS --
THINGS WILL BE DIFFERENT

31:16.755 --> 31:19.168
NOW THAT
SHE CAN BE AMANDA.

31:19.168 --> 31:22.001
I MEAN, MY GOD,
JUST GIVE HER ONE MORE CHANCE.

31:22.001 --> 31:24.423
NO. I TOLD HER
I WOULDN'T WAIT.

31:28.097 --> 31:31.931
I'M ASKING YOU
AS A FRIEND...

31:31.931 --> 31:35.104
DON'T EVER TELL ME
THAT SHE LOVES ME AGAIN.

31:49.078 --> 31:51.290
I'LL CALL YOU
WHEN I GET TO L.A.

31:54.833 --> 31:56.835
[ INSECTS CHIRPING ]

32:03.342 --> 32:04.543
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

32:09.638 --> 32:12.641
I WANTED TO SEE YOU
BEFORE I LEFT.

32:12.641 --> 32:15.604
HOW DID TODAY GO?

32:15.604 --> 32:18.187
UH,
I-I DIDN'T TELL HER.

32:18.187 --> 32:21.560
I COULDN'T.
SHE WAS SO HAPPY.

32:21.560 --> 32:24.483
FOR 20 YEARS, THAT WAS
ALL I EVER DREAMED OF.

32:24.483 --> 32:27.026
HOW WAS I SUPPOSED TO
RUIN THAT MOMENT?

32:27.026 --> 32:31.410
YOU KNOW, SINCE BEING BACK,
UH...I ALWAYS THOUGHT

32:31.410 --> 32:34.833
THAT I'D BEEN GIVEN
A NEW LEASE ON LIFE.

32:34.833 --> 32:37.626
MAYBE I WAS WRONG.

32:37.626 --> 32:41.880
MAYBE IT WAS ALL JUST
A LONG SETUP TO A SICK JOKE.

32:41.880 --> 32:44.213
THAT'S A LOAD OF BULL.

32:44.213 --> 32:46.385
YOU DIDN'T FIGHT
TO SURVIVE THAT HELL

32:46.385 --> 32:49.008
JUST TO BE
FATE'S PUNCH LINE.

32:49.008 --> 32:51.510
YOU'RE HERE FOR A REASON,
DAVID.

32:51.510 --> 32:54.893
YOU MAY NOT BELIEVE IT NOW,
BUT YOU WILL,

32:54.893 --> 32:57.896
WHICH IS WHY
YOU NEED TO KEEP FIGHTING.

33:01.270 --> 33:02.901
TAKE THIS.

33:02.901 --> 33:05.064
IT'S THE NUMBER
FOR A FRIEND OF MINE

33:05.064 --> 33:07.816
WHO HAPPENS TO BE THE BEST
ONCOLOGIST YOU'LL EVER MEET.

33:10.109 --> 33:11.490
WHAT'S THE OTHER NUMBER?

33:11.490 --> 33:13.112
MINE.

33:14.783 --> 33:17.116
YOU'RE NOT
DOING THIS ALONE.

33:22.581 --> 33:24.002
Nolan: EMILY!

33:24.002 --> 33:26.215
[ PANTING ]
I'VE BEEN CALLING YOU.

33:26.215 --> 33:27.386
WHY DIDN'T YOU PICK UP?
 MY PHONE WAS OFF.

33:27.386 --> 33:28.587
WHAT'S WRONG?

33:28.587 --> 33:31.470
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]
JACK'S LEAVING.

33:31.470 --> 33:33.682
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
"LEAVING"?

33:33.682 --> 33:36.185
RIGHT NOW.
HE'S LEAVING TOWN FOR GOOD.

33:36.185 --> 33:39.188
BUT...WELL,
HE DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING.

33:39.188 --> 33:42.061
WELL, WHY WOULD HE?
HE'S ALREADY SAID EVERYTHING.

33:42.061 --> 33:43.272
I MEAN,
DID YOU REALLY TELL HIM

33:43.272 --> 33:45.023
THAT YOU DIDN'T
WANT TO BE WITH HIM?

33:45.023 --> 33:47.146
I SAID THAT
I CAN'T BE WITH HIM.

33:47.146 --> 33:49.068
LISTEN TO YOURSELF,
EMS.

33:49.068 --> 33:51.700
HOW MANY TIMES DID YOU THINK
YOU COULD PUSH HIM AWAY

33:51.700 --> 33:53.322
BEFORE
HE FINALLY BROKE?

33:53.322 --> 33:54.533
WHAT WAS I SUPPOSED TO DO,
NOLAN?

33:54.533 --> 33:56.155
YOU KNOW HOW MUCH
HE'S SUFFERED BECAUSE OF ME.

33:56.155 --> 33:59.078
AND STILL HE CHOSE YOU.

33:59.078 --> 34:02.040
HE LOVES YOU, EMS.

34:02.040 --> 34:04.213
HE HAD THE GUTS
TO OPEN HIS HEART.

34:04.213 --> 34:05.584
CAN YOU?

34:05.584 --> 34:08.587
HONESTLY, DO YOU EVEN KNOW
WHAT YOU REALLY WANT?

34:08.587 --> 34:10.549
ALL RIGHT, WELL,
LET ME HELP YOU OUT,

34:10.549 --> 34:12.170
BECAUSE SOMETIMES
IT'S HARD

34:12.170 --> 34:14.052
TO SEE WHAT'S
RIGHT IN FRONT OF YOUR EYES.

34:14.052 --> 34:18.056
THE ONLY THING STOPPING YOU
FROM CHOOSING JACK IS YOU.

34:18.056 --> 34:20.389
I KNOW.

34:20.389 --> 34:22.060
BUT I DON'T DESERVE HIM!

34:24.062 --> 34:25.893
BUT YOU DESERVE ME?

34:27.606 --> 34:28.817
BEN, I'M SORRY.

34:28.817 --> 34:31.029
WHY, BECAUSE I FINALLY
HEARD THE TRUTH?

34:31.029 --> 34:33.322
LOOK, THIS IS SO MUCH
MORE COMPLICA--

34:33.322 --> 34:35.072
WILL YOU TALK TO ME
LIKE A PERSON, PLEASE?

34:36.195 --> 34:37.576
I FEEL LIKE I'VE EARNED
AT LEAST THAT MUCH.

34:40.038 --> 34:42.201
DO YOU WANT THIS TO WORK
OR NOT?

34:45.754 --> 34:48.167
WELL, I GUESS
THERE'S OUR ANSWER.

34:48.167 --> 34:50.168
BEN, WAIT.
 WHAT?

34:50.168 --> 34:52.380
THE TRUTH'S OUT,
EMILY.

34:52.380 --> 34:56.844
YOU WERE JUST HIDING WITH ME.
YOU WEREN'T LIVING.

34:56.844 --> 35:00.098
AND DEEP DOWN,
I KNEW IT...

35:00.098 --> 35:03.142
BUT I GUESS I DIDN'T WANT TO
FACE REALITY, EITHER.

35:04.893 --> 35:07.105
[ SIGHS ]

35:12.151 --> 35:15.154
JACK'S FLIGHT LEAVES
IN 20 MINUTES.

35:15.154 --> 35:17.786
IF YOU WANT TO STOP HIM,

35:17.786 --> 35:21.160
YOU NEED TO MAKE YOUR DECISION
RIGHT NOW.

35:29.878 --> 35:34.092
YOU SURE ABOUT THIS?
NO REGRETS?

35:34.092 --> 35:36.094
NO, NO REGRETS.

35:36.094 --> 35:39.097
THAT MAKES ME HAPPY,
JACK.

35:39.097 --> 35:42.100
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]
 HEY, CARL! CARL!

35:42.100 --> 35:44.102
WAIT FOR ME.

35:44.102 --> 35:46.064
LET'S GO ON THE PLANE.

35:46.064 --> 35:48.106
[ BEEP ]

35:48.106 --> 35:49.147
LET'S DO THIS.

35:49.147 --> 35:51.029
[ BEEP ]

36:03.081 --> 36:07.286
I DIDN'T GET A CHANCE TO SEE YOU
AT THE CLUB BEFORE I LEFT.

36:07.286 --> 36:10.709
WELL, AFTER THE DESTRUCTION
CAUSED BY HURRICANE LOUISE,

36:10.709 --> 36:14.713
I...I DIDN'T THINK
I'D BE SEEING YOU AGAIN EVER.

36:14.713 --> 36:18.136
IT'S YOUR SUIT,
REMEMBER?

36:18.136 --> 36:21.720
[ SIGHS ] LOOK,
I KNOW YOU -- YOU'RE MAD.

36:21.720 --> 36:23.722
I MEAN,
YOU HAVE EVERY RIGHT TO BE.

36:23.722 --> 36:26.475
I HOSTED
 THE WORST FUNDRAISER EVER

36:26.475 --> 36:27.896
AND RUINED YOUR RELATIONSHIP
WITH --

36:27.896 --> 36:29.438
HEY, HEY, HEY,
SLOW DOWN.

36:29.438 --> 36:31.520
LOOK, TODAY DIDN'T GO
AS PLANNED, NO QUESTION,

36:31.520 --> 36:34.573
AND I DO HAVE SOME DAMAGE
CONTROL TO DO WITH MY BOSS.

36:34.573 --> 36:36.315
BUT WE STILL RAISED MONEY
FOR THE KIDS.

36:36.315 --> 36:38.076
THAT'S
THE IMPORTANT THING.

36:39.988 --> 36:43.161
HUH.
I ASSUMED YOU'D BE PISSED.

36:43.161 --> 36:46.164
I WAS,
BUT NOT AT YOU.

36:46.164 --> 36:49.378
LOUISE IS A LUNATIC,
BUT SHE WAS A SIDESHOW.

36:49.378 --> 36:52.000
THE MAIN EVENT WAS YOU,

36:52.000 --> 36:56.004
A MAN TRYING TO DO SOMETHING
GOOD, NOT -- NOT DESTRUCTIVE.

36:56.004 --> 36:58.597
AND DESPITE HER WORST
INTENTIONS, YOU SUCCEEDED.

36:58.597 --> 37:01.099
WOW.

37:01.099 --> 37:02.261
THIS IS NOT AT ALL

37:02.261 --> 37:05.103
HOW I IMAGINED THIS CONVERSATION
WAS GONNA GO.

37:05.103 --> 37:09.848
USUALLY, MY FRIENDS START
UNCAPPING THE RED SHARPIE

37:09.848 --> 37:12.190
RIGHT ABOUT NOW.

37:12.190 --> 37:13.982
MAYBE IT'S TIME

37:13.982 --> 37:16.405
YOU STARTED LOOKING AT LIFE
FROM A DIFFERENT PERSPECTIVE.

37:16.405 --> 37:20.909
BECAUSE FROM THIS VIEW,
IT LOOKS PRETTY GREAT.

37:22.821 --> 37:26.034
I'VE NEVER MET ANYONE
LIKE YOU.

37:26.034 --> 37:28.036
NOW YOU HAVE.

37:40.679 --> 37:43.051
Louise: [ SIGHS ] I DIDN'T KNOW
WHERE ELSE TO GO.

37:43.051 --> 37:47.055
I CAN'T GET AHOLD OF VICTORIA,
AND I'M WORRIED ABOUT HER.

37:47.055 --> 37:49.187
I KNOW. ME TOO.

37:49.187 --> 37:51.480
I WAS WITH HER EARLIER.

37:51.480 --> 37:56.485
SHE SEEMED SO DIFFERENT --
DEFEATED.

37:56.485 --> 37:58.026
AND YOU LEFT HER?

37:58.026 --> 38:00.529
WELL, SHE WAS
WITH HER BODYGUARD.

38:00.529 --> 38:03.111
I MADE HER PROMISE
TO CALL ME TOMORROW.

38:05.073 --> 38:07.456
SOMETHING IS NOT RIGHT
WITH HER.

38:07.456 --> 38:10.038
[ SIGHS ]
I FEEL SO HELPLESS.

38:10.038 --> 38:12.461
I TRIED TO GET NOLAN TO ADMIT
THAT HE AND EMILY

38:12.461 --> 38:14.543
WERE BEHIND THE WHOLE THING
TODAY, BUT --

38:14.543 --> 38:17.175
OH, THEY'RE TOO CLEVER
TO FALL FOR THAT.

38:17.175 --> 38:20.178
BUT THEY WILL
MAKE A MISTAKE,

38:20.178 --> 38:22.471
AND WE WILL BE THERE
TO CATCH THEM.

38:22.471 --> 38:25.133
WE?

38:25.133 --> 38:28.096
I CAN GET PAST
OUR HISTORY...

38:28.096 --> 38:31.099
IF YOU CAN --
FOR VICTORIA.

38:31.099 --> 38:33.932
[ GLASSES CLINK ]

38:33.932 --> 38:36.064
I HOPE
SHE'S ALL RIGHT TONIGHT.

39:18.607 --> 39:20.609
[ GAS HISSING ]

39:54.563 --> 39:55.564
[ SIGHS ]

39:55.564 --> 39:58.647
[ CAR APPROACHES ]

40:00.819 --> 40:03.111
[ CAR DOOR OPENS ]

40:08.196 --> 40:09.828
AWW.

40:09.828 --> 40:11.580
YOU MISSED YOUR FLIGHT.

40:11.580 --> 40:13.161
[ LAUGHS ]

40:13.161 --> 40:15.584
SEEING THAT LOOK
ON YOUR FACE

40:15.584 --> 40:17.796
ALMOST MAKES
THE PAST YEAR WORTHWHILE,

40:17.796 --> 40:19.998
THE KEY WORD
BEING "ALMOST."

40:19.998 --> 40:22.210
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE,
MASON?

40:22.210 --> 40:23.592
WE HAD A DEAL.

40:23.592 --> 40:25.173
YES, WE DID.

40:25.173 --> 40:29.758
AND I WAS WAITING PATIENTLY,
TYPING AWAY ON MY MAGNUM OPUS --

40:29.758 --> 40:32.350
"THE SECRET ORIGIN
OF EMILY THORNE."

40:32.350 --> 40:34.142
SO IMAGINE MY SURPRISE

40:34.142 --> 40:36.144
WHEN I CAUGHT
YOUR HEARTFELT PERFORMANCE,

40:36.144 --> 40:42.060
ANNOUNCING TO ALL THE WORLD THAT
VERY SAME STORY -- MY STORY.

40:42.060 --> 40:45.233
I HAD NO CHOICE.
EVERYTHING CHANGED.

40:45.233 --> 40:48.567
YES,
EVERYTHING BUT YOU.

40:50.198 --> 40:53.832
WHICH I SUPPOSE IS JUST NOW
STARTING TO BECOME APPARENT,

40:53.832 --> 40:57.165
STANDING THERE ALONE
ON THE TARMAC,

40:57.165 --> 41:01.880
REALIZING THAT WHILE YOU HID
BEHIND YOUR MISSION OF REVENGE,

41:01.880 --> 41:04.843
EVERYONE ELSE AROUND YOU
EVOLVED.

41:04.843 --> 41:07.846
DID YOU REALLY THINK
THEY'D WAIT FOREVER,

41:07.846 --> 41:12.140
SACRIFICING EVERYTHING
AND GETTING NOTHING IN RETURN?

41:12.140 --> 41:14.723
DID YOU HONESTLY BELIEVE

41:14.723 --> 41:18.356
THAT YOU'D GET
YOUR "HAPPILY EVER AFTER"

41:18.356 --> 41:23.732
AFTER SO MANY LIES
TO SO MANY DIFFERENT PEOPLE...

41:23.732 --> 41:28.276
UNTIL ALL YOU HAD LEFT
WERE ENEMIES?

41:28.276 --> 41:32.280
LIKE THE LITTLE PYROMANIAC
THAT YOU ARE, YOU STARTED A FIRE

